<h2 id="a-single-slit">A Single Slit</h2>

<p>Because our model is corpuscular, we don‚Äôt have diffraction.</p>

<p><img src="/resources/2016-06-01/img/small_slit-phitheta.png" /></p>

<p><img src="/resources/2016-06-01/img/small_slit-pattern.png" /></p>

<h2 id="a-double-slit">A Double Slit</h2>

<p>Again, no diffraction. The pattern that occurs is mostly an aliasing effect.</p>

<p><img src="/resources/2016-06-01/img/double_slit-phitheta.png" /></p>

<p><img src="/resources/2016-06-01/img/double_slit-pattern.png" /></p>

<h2 id="negative-slit">Negative Slit</h2>

<p>Our model is flexible enough to allow for ‚Äúnegative transparency‚Äù, when ‚Äúnegative light‚Äù is projected forwards while extra light is reflected backwards. This is basically just a color inverted version of a small reflector.</p>

<p><img src="/resources/2016-06-01/img/negative_slit-phitheta.png" /></p>

<p><img src="/resources/2016-06-01/img/negative_slit-pattern.png" /></p>

